2026 Regular Session ENROLLED
SENATE BILL NO. 150
BY SENATOR BOUDREAUX AND REPRESENTATIVE CHASSION
1 AN ACT
2 To enact R.S. 40:42.1, relative to vital records; to provide for the scanning of documents;
3 to provide for the creation of electronic files; to provide for the issuance of certified
4 copies of documents; to provide for an effective date; and to provide for related
5 matters.
6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
7 Section 1. R.S. 40:42.1 is hereby enacted to read as follows:
8 §42.1. Scanning of original supporting documents and creation of electronic
9 files; issuance of certified copies of evidentiary documents
10 A. The vital records registry and the state registrar may scan original
11 documents submitted in support of vital records applications and in
12 substantiation of information contained in the vital records registry,
13 electronically store the scanned original documents, and return the original
14 documents to the submitter. The scanned and electronically stored originals
15 shall have the same authenticity as the original documents.
16 B. The vital records registry and the state registrar may issue certified
17 copies of documents in their custody in paper or electronic form, including but
18 not limited to those that are evidentiary in nature.
19 Section 2. This Act shall become effective upon signature by the governor or, if not
20 signed by the governor, upon expiration of the time for bills to become law without signature
